  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">A relevant relation between the dwell time and the density of states for a three dimensional system of arbitrary shape with an arbitrary number of incoming channel is derived. This result extends the one obtained by Gasparian et al. for the special case of a layered one dimensional symmetrical system. We believe that such a strong relation between the most widely accepted time related to the dynamics of a particle and the density of states in the barrier region, one of the most relevant properties of a system in equilibrium, is rich of physical significance.</subfield>
